      "content": "thanks for the code. that makes sense. one thing though, i noticed in the logs that sometimes the order objects seem to persist even after we think we've cleared the queue, or they just disappear without the destructor being called in some edge cases. if the memory is still climbing, could there be some other hidden way a reference is being held onto somewhere else in the system? how would i track down where those orphaned objects are coming from?",
